                                 Release Notes
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Twenty years after her landmark Watermark album, Enya's seventh studio disc, And 
Winter Came continues a phenomenally successful career that has included more than 
70 million albums sold worldwide. And Winter Came is an enchanting evocation of 
the changing landscape of winter as well as the festive cheer of the holidays. 
One of the most successful female artists of all-time, and second only to U2 as 
the biggest selling Irish artist in history, Enya brings her beguiling and ethereal 
music to bear on the darkest and yet most hopeful season with And Winter Came.
